title: My intensely cranky elbows have lost most of their crank.
text:
And I mean, they hurt. The first use, the change was dynamic, 2nd use, gone. I'm a guy, loved backyard sports (50 years ago), & the arms & hands remind me often. The hands are a little tougher for relief. Tendonitis seems eased, and oh yeah -- migraines -- mine are day and nightly, every -- part of ptsd. I put it mostly on sides of the neck and that chord going up behind the ears, that gets so tight. Follow that chord down into your shoulders. The temples don't seems as helpful for me (but do them!).
I don't know if this is the best product, but for the money I spent, I'd buy it again. Oh yeah, it doesn't take much to work. Put it on the end of 2 fingers, and you can tell how much it takes.

Update: I don't mean to make you think this'll make it all go away. Getting old sucks, & chronic pain is just that. I've tried the Ben-gays & a lot of others, to less avail; I've tried painkillers, & Aleve , but I hesitate -- it's an N-Said -- but it takes the inflamation/pain away, for me, for days or weeks (I think naproxin is the name of the script, which I've heard is safe). The headaches -- no question -- are a life ruining condition and I empathize. Aleve doesn't touch it, but magnesium helps. Remember that life is the gift, & this is part of it, for us. So much for philosophy.

title: Quality but don't pay more for custom size
text:
Item arrived and it is beautiful. Seller raised the cost to make it fit two notebooks, I told him the brand and tried to send link to Amazon to show him but Amazon removed the link. So from the page I copied the size the page says it is. As it's from a different country, we waited patiently for the item to arrive. It arrived and it's quality leather. It's darker than the picture, I okayed it darker than expected when seller let me know ahead of time that it wouldn't match the color as shown as the batch was dyed darker. The stitches are nice and even. I would have put the personalization (name) not so far to the edge but that's a personal preference. The design is hard to see as the dye batch was dark. It's real leather and it looks high quality. I took off two stars because it didn't fit the two BooQool notebooks which I had paid more so he'd be sure they fit. He asked me to take a picture to show it doesn't fit. I think he forgot when measurements are given, it doesn't include the hard cover (that's what I learned before how to read the measurements but that's my research on what is A5 etc size). I had originally planned to order a second one for myself but was not happy with how the two journals didn't fit (one barely fit so there was not way both would have fit!); the seller assured me he can make them both fit and he increased the cost on Amazon to cover for larger size.
So if you want fine craftsmanship but take your chances on it fitting particular notebooks (even custom order as mine was, even giving the item name on Amazon), I would recommend the seller. If there is an issue though, that's is the chance you take.

title: Smells great in the bag
text: Opening the bag, the scent was great and I was excited to try it out. I fill the tub, got in, and realized there were no instructions on the bag, so not knowing how much I was supposed to use, I dumped about a cup in. It fizzed on impact, but very quickly settled down. Within minutes, the scent was gone and I was left with just slightly opaque salt water. I dumped in about another half cup, which brought the scent back for a few more minutes, but it again faded quickly. The listing mentions being an Epsom Salt, and that's essentially the experience. I know it's not a bath bomb, so I wasn't expecting much in terms on the fizzing, but I figured I'd at least get to enjoy the scent for awhile and maybe get the water a cool color, but very quickly, I was just sitting in an Epsom Salt bath with none of the fun I expected.

title: Nice print on heavy poster stock, definitely a night view of Disney World's Magic Kingdom
text:
This poster arrives well-packaged and it's nicely printed on heavy photo-style card stock. It's definitely a high-quality print.

The photo is clear and a great view of Disney World's Cinderella castle, with the statue of Walt and Mickey in front of it.

In real life, the photo is darker than I expected, but - looking at the photo on the Amazon page - it is a 100% match.

If, like us, you're displaying this against white walls, this print may look best in a dark or black frame, so - by contrast (literally) - the photo doesn't look quite so dark.

For a very clear, night view of the Cinderella castle, this is an excellent choice. It's what you'd see at Disney World, shortly before the nightly fireworks start.

This is a high-quality print, just not as bright as I'd expected, and that's an issue of personal taste.

title: Pricey costume jewelry
text:
As the listing implies, this is a dainty necklace. No problem there, as I wanted something smaller in size. However, I think the fact that it is dainty allowed the manufacturer to sort of haphazardly create the charm. It looks great in its box, but much less so when it's taken out if the packaging. It's not as beautiful in person than the listing shows. Perhaps someone with a less discerning eye would appreciate this necklace, but I'm not a fan of the price for what is essentially just regular old costume jewelry.
Additionally, there are instructions on how to keep this piece looking nice, such as keeping it dry. I dread to think what would happen if one began to sweat while wearing it. I would rather put the $40+ toward a genuine gold necklace that can withstand much more.

title: Artwork is nice, classy even!
text: This clock was purchased for pool side use.  It's positioned under the overhang on our porch/deck near the pool.  It hasn't rained since we got it, but I don't think it will get wet under there anyhow.  This clock doesn't have glass over the face of it, and I think the seller mentioned that it's not meant to get wet.  My deck normally doesn't get wet there. But if the weather gets that crazy, I'll bring it in.  The clock arrived sooner than anticipated and was packed in a cardboard box that had little styrofoam blocks to hold it place.  It was well packaged. The numbers are extremely legible, even from a distance when I'm in the pool. And the artwork is nice, classy even.  I put one double A battery in it as soon as it arrived and it's been keeping great time - better than the clock in the kitchen from Home Depot. The seller cautions you to use the little winder thingy in the back to set the time, rather than just moving the hands of the clock in the front. (I was tempted, but I did it correctly.)  I'm glad I got this.
